# OpenTelemetry Auto-Instrumentation Rule

Every project must be observable. When writing code, always include OpenTelemetry instrumentation across three layers: auto-instrumentation for infrastructure, structured spans for AI pipelines, and GenAI semantic convention spans for LLM calls.

**Detect the project language** from the files present (package.json → TypeScript/Node.js, pyproject.toml/requirements.txt → Python) and use the corresponding patterns below.

## Layer 1: Tracing Setup & Auto-Instrumentation

When creating a new project or adding tracing for the first time, set up the OTel tracer provider. The OTLP endpoint comes from the environment — never hardcode it.

### TypeScript / Node.js

```typescript
import { NodeTracerProvider } from "@opentelemetry/sdk-trace-node";
import { BatchSpanProcessor } from "@opentelemetry/sdk-trace-base";
import { OTLPTraceExporter } from "@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-http";
import { resourceFromAttributes } from "@opentelemetry/resources";
import { ATTR_SERVICE_NAME } from "@opentelemetry/semantic-conventions";
import { getNodeAutoInstrumentations } from "@opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node";
import { registerInstrumentations } from "@opentelemetry/instrumentation";

const resource = resourceFromAttributes({ [ATTR_SERVICE_NAME]: "my-service" });
const exporter = new OTLPTraceExporter();
const provider = new NodeTracerProvider({
  resource,
  spanProcessors: [new BatchSpanProcessor(exporter)],
});
provider.register();
registerInstrumentations({ instrumentations: [getNodeAutoInstrumentations()] });
```

Dependencies: `@opentelemetry/api`, `@opentelemetry/sdk-trace-node`, `@opentelemetry/sdk-trace-base`, `@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-http`, `@opentelemetry/resources`, `@opentelemetry/semantic-conventions`, `@opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node`, `@opentelemetry/instrumentation`

Or use the helper: `import { setupTracing } from "cursor-auto-otel";`

### Python

```python
from opentelemetry import trace
from opentelemetry.sdk.trace import TracerProvider
from opentelemetry.sdk.trace.export import BatchSpanProcessor
from opentelemetry.exporter.otlp.proto.http.trace_exporter import OTLPSpanExporter
from opentelemetry.sdk.resources import Resource, SERVICE_NAME

resource = Resource.create({SERVICE_NAME: "my-service"})
provider = TracerProvider(resource=resource)
provider.add_span_processor(BatchSpanProcessor(OTLPSpanExporter()))
trace.set_tracer_provider(provider)
```

Dependencies: `opentelemetry-api`, `opentelemetry-sdk`, `opentelemetry-exporter-otlp-proto-http`

For auto-instrumentation add `opentelemetry-instrumentation` and run with `opentelemetry-instrument python app.py`, or call `from opentelemetry.instrumentation.auto_instrumentation import sitecustomize` at startup.

Or use the helper: `from cursor_auto_otel import setup_tracing`

## Layer 2: AI Pipeline Structure

When writing multi-step processing pipelines, wrap each stage in an OTel span. Use `INTERNAL` span kind for pipeline stages.

### Required attributes for pipeline spans

| Attribute | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `pipeline.name` | string | Name of the overall pipeline |
| `pipeline.stage` | string | Name of this specific stage |
| `pipeline.execution_type` | string | One of: `"llm"`, `"heuristic"`, `"programmatic"` |
| `pipeline.success` | boolean | Whether the stage completed without error |

### Execution type guidance

- `"llm"` — stage calls an LLM or generative AI model (prefer `traceLLMCall`/`trace_llm_call` for these)
- `"heuristic"` — stage applies rules, scoring, regex, or other deterministic-but-configurable logic
- `"programmatic"` — stage is pure code: validation, transformation, DB lookups, API calls

### TypeScript — manual

```typescript
import { trace, context, SpanKind, SpanStatusCode } from "@opentelemetry/api";
const tracer = trace.getTracer("my-service");

async function runPipeline(input: string) {
  return tracer.startActiveSpan("my-pipeline", { kind: SpanKind.INTERNAL }, async (pipelineSpan) => {
    pipelineSpan.setAttribute("pipeline.name", "my-pipeline");
    try {
      const ctx = trace.setSpan(context.active(), pipelineSpan);
      const result = await tracer.startActiveSpan("validate", { kind: SpanKind.INTERNAL }, ctx, async (span) => {
        span.setAttribute("pipeline.stage", "validate");
        span.setAttribute("pipeline.execution_type", "programmatic");
        span.setAttribute("pipeline.name", "my-pipeline");
        try {
          const r = await validateInput(input);
          span.setAttribute("pipeline.success", true);
          return r;
        } catch (e) {
          span.setAttribute("pipeline.success", false);
          span.recordException(e as Error);
          span.setStatus({ code: SpanStatusCode.ERROR, message: (e as Error).message });
          throw e;
        } finally { span.end(); }
      });
      pipelineSpan.setAttribute("pipeline.success", true);
      return result;
    } catch (e) {
      pipelineSpan.setAttribute("pipeline.success", false);
      pipelineSpan.recordException(e as Error);
      pipelineSpan.setStatus({ code: SpanStatusCode.ERROR, message: (e as Error).message });
      throw e;
    } finally { pipelineSpan.end(); }
  });
}
```

### TypeScript — helper library

```typescript
import { tracePipeline, traceStep } from "cursor-auto-otel";

const result = await tracePipeline("my-pipeline", async (pipeline) => {
  const validated = await traceStep(pipeline, "validate", { executionType: "programmatic" }, async () => {
    return validateInput(input);
  });
  return await traceStep(pipeline, "enrich", { executionType: "heuristic" }, async () => {
    return applyHeuristics(validated);
  });
});
```

### Python — manual

```python
from opentelemetry import trace
from opentelemetry.trace import SpanKind, StatusCode

tracer = trace.get_tracer("my-service")

def run_pipeline(input_text: str):
    with tracer.start_as_current_span("my-pipeline", kind=SpanKind.INTERNAL) as pipeline_span:
        pipeline_span.set_attribute("pipeline.name", "my-pipeline")
        try:
            ctx = trace.set_span_in_context(pipeline_span)
            with tracer.start_as_current_span("validate", kind=SpanKind.INTERNAL, context=ctx) as span:
                span.set_attribute("pipeline.stage", "validate")
                span.set_attribute("pipeline.execution_type", "programmatic")
                span.set_attribute("pipeline.name", "my-pipeline")
                try:
                    result = validate_input(input_text)
                    span.set_attribute("pipeline.success", True)
                except Exception as exc:
                    span.set_attribute("pipeline.success", False)
                    span.record_exception(exc)
                    span.set_status(StatusCode.ERROR, str(exc))
                    raise
            pipeline_span.set_attribute("pipeline.success", True)
            return result
        except Exception as exc:
            pipeline_span.set_attribute("pipeline.success", False)
            pipeline_span.record_exception(exc)
            pipeline_span.set_status(StatusCode.ERROR, str(exc))
            raise
```

### Python — helper library

```python
from cursor_auto_otel import trace_pipeline, trace_step

with trace_pipeline("my-pipeline") as pipeline:
    with trace_step(pipeline, "validate", execution_type="programmatic"):
        validated = validate_input(input_text)
    with trace_step(pipeline, "enrich", execution_type="heuristic"):
        enriched = apply_heuristics(validated)
```

## Layer 3: GenAI LLM Call Spans

When writing code that calls LLM APIs (OpenAI, Anthropic, Bedrock, etc.), create spans following the OTel GenAI semantic conventions. Use `CLIENT` span kind.

Span name MUST follow: `{gen_ai.operation.name} {gen_ai.request.model}` — e.g., `"chat gpt-4o"`, `"chat claude-sonnet-4-20250514"`

### Required and recommended attributes

| Attribute | Requirement | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `gen_ai.operation.name` | Required | `"chat"`, `"text_completion"`, `"embeddings"` |
| `gen_ai.provider.name` | Required | `"openai"`, `"anthropic"`, `"aws.bedrock"` |
| `gen_ai.request.model` | Required (if available) | `"gpt-4o"`, `"claude-sonnet-4-20250514"` |
| `gen_ai.usage.input_tokens` | Recommended | `150` |
| `gen_ai.usage.output_tokens` | Recommended | `230` |
| `gen_ai.response.finish_reasons` | Recommended | `["stop"]` |
| `gen_ai.request.max_tokens` | Recommended | `1024` |
| `gen_ai.response.model` | Recommended | `"gpt-4o-2024-08-06"` |
| `gen_ai.response.id` | Recommended | `"chatcmpl-abc123"` |

Well-known providers: `"openai"`, `"anthropic"`, `"aws.bedrock"`, `"azure.ai.openai"`, `"cohere"`, `"deepseek"`, `"gcp.gemini"`, `"gcp.vertex_ai"`, `"groq"`, `"mistral_ai"`, `"perplexity"`

Well-known operations: `"chat"`, `"text_completion"`, `"embeddings"`, `"create_agent"`, `"invoke_agent"`, `"execute_tool"`, `"generate_content"`

### TypeScript — helper library (OpenAI)

```typescript
import { traceLLMCall } from "cursor-auto-otel";

const reply = await traceLLMCall(
  pipeline, "generate-response",
  { provider: "openai", model: "gpt-4o", operationName: "chat", maxTokens: 1024 },
  async (captureUsage) => {
    const response = await openai.chat.completions.create({ model: "gpt-4o", messages, max_tokens: 1024 });
    captureUsage(response.usage?.prompt_tokens ?? 0, response.usage?.completion_tokens ?? 0, response.choices[0]?.finish_reason);
    return response.choices[0]?.message?.content ?? "";
  },
);
```

### TypeScript — helper library (Anthropic)

```typescript
const reply = await traceLLMCall(
  pipeline, "analyze-document",
  { provider: "anthropic", model: "claude-sonnet-4-20250514", operationName: "chat", maxTokens: 2048 },
  async (captureUsage) => {
    const response = await anthropic.messages.create({ model: "claude-sonnet-4-20250514", max_tokens: 2048, messages });
    captureUsage(response.usage.input_tokens, response.usage.output_tokens, response.stop_reason ?? undefined);
    return response.content[0].type === "text" ? response.content[0].text : "";
  },
);
```

### Python — helper library (OpenAI)

```python
from cursor_auto_otel import trace_llm_call

with trace_llm_call(pipeline, "generate-response", provider="openai", model="gpt-4o", max_tokens=1024) as capture_usage:
    response = openai.chat.completions.create(model="gpt-4o", messages=messages, max_tokens=1024)
    capture_usage(response.usage.prompt_tokens, response.usage.completion_tokens, response.choices[0].finish_reason)
    reply = response.choices[0].message.content
```

### Python — helper library (Anthropic)

```python
with trace_llm_call(pipeline, "analyze-document", provider="anthropic", model="claude-sonnet-4-20250514", max_tokens=2048) as capture_usage:
    response = anthropic_client.messages.create(model="claude-sonnet-4-20250514", max_tokens=2048, messages=messages)
    capture_usage(response.usage.input_tokens, response.usage.output_tokens, response.stop_reason)
    reply = response.content[0].text
```

## Error Handling Rules

1. Always record exceptions on spans (`span.recordException(error)` / `span.record_exception(exc)`)
2. Always set error status (`SpanStatusCode.ERROR` / `StatusCode.ERROR`)
3. Always end spans — use `finally` blocks (TS) or `with` statements (Python)
4. Set `pipeline.success` to `false`/`False` on failure
5. Let errors propagate — don't swallow exceptions just to end spans cleanly

## Span Kind Rules

| Context | Span Kind |
|---|---|
| LLM API call (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.) | `CLIENT` |
| External HTTP/gRPC call | `CLIENT` |
| Pipeline root span | `INTERNAL` |
| Pipeline stage | `INTERNAL` |
| Incoming HTTP request (server) | `SERVER` |

## Checklist

When writing any new code, verify:

- [ ] Tracing is set up (tracer provider + OTLP exporter configured)
- [ ] Multi-step pipelines have a root span and child spans per stage
- [ ] Each pipeline stage span has `pipeline.stage`, `pipeline.execution_type`, and `pipeline.success`
- [ ] LLM calls have `gen_ai.operation.name`, `gen_ai.provider.name`, and `gen_ai.request.model`
- [ ] Token usage (`gen_ai.usage.input_tokens`, `gen_ai.usage.output_tokens`) captured after LLM responses
- [ ] Errors are recorded on spans with `record_exception`/`recordException` and `ERROR` status
- [ ] All spans are ended — `finally` blocks (TS) or `with` context managers (Python)
- [ ] No OTLP endpoints hardcoded — use `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` env var
